This paper deals with privacy-preserving spatial analytics, which involves mining spatial data. This topic is closely related to databases (cs.DB) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of differential privacy, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces novel techniques for counting planar regions, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and topology (cs.CY).
